{
  "texts": [
    "While the automatic maps cannot always provide a close match, their characteristics are often within the distributions inferred from human-made maps (Fig. 5).",
    "We emphasize that this comparison only seeks to identify the differences between automatic maps and their human counterparts.",
    "This is a different matter from correctness, as human-made maps can also be fallible.",
    "For example, the trained human reader for Obesity-2014P failed to find a single cycle, whereas the GPT-based system identified several.",
    "In this paper, we examined the feasibility of using GPT-3.5 to extract causal maps from text."
  ]
}